fields.name: measRate
fields.description: The elapsed time between GNSS measurements, which defines the rate, e.g. 100 ms => 10 Hz. Measurement rate should be greater than or equal to 25 ms (50 ms for protocol versions < 24.00).

fields.name: navRate
fields.description: The ratio between the number of measurements and the number of navigation solutions. Max value 127.

fields.name: timeRef
fields.description: The time system to which measurements are aligned: 0 = UTC, 1 = GPS, 2 = GLONASS, 3 = BeiDou, 4 = Galileo, 5 = NavIC

issues: Labeled byte offset 4 as 'reserved0' instead of 'timeRef'. Given the protocol version 24.00 reference in the description, this field is defined in this manual version.
Represents an older protocol version where NavIC (timeRef 5) was not yet supported/documented.
Represents an older protocol version without NavIC support in timeRef.

valid_variations.reason: Protocol versions prior to 29.00 do not support NavIC (value 5) as a time reference.

adjudication.reasoning: The message UBX-CFG-RATE is highly consistent across generations (M8, M9, F9). It is always 6 bytes. The primary evolution is in the 'timeRef' field at offset 4, which expanded to include NavIC in protocol version 29.00. Extraction 1 failed to identify 'timeRef', likely treating it as reserved due to a parsing error or a simplified source table, despite the text referencing protocol versions that clearly support it. Extractions 3 and 6 correctly reflect the state of the protocol at their respective publication times (pre-NavIC).
